Adding command in the U-boot 
===========================
1.for adding the led driver in u-boot cpoy the led.c file in the drivers/led/

2. in drivwrs/led/ give "vi Makefile" and add the onj file in the Makefile
     obj-y += sled.o

3. add kconfig in the same location by giving the "vi Kconfig"

config SLED
        bool "SLED support for LEDs"
        depends on LED
        help
          Enable support for LEDs which are connected to GPIO lines. These
          GPIOs may be on the SoC or some other device which provides GPIOs.
          The GPIO driver must used driver model. LEDs are configured using
          the device tree.

4.

